      "label": "Condition",
      "value": "Badly preserved papyrus. None of the original cutting lines have been preserved. There are many holes causing much damage to the text. In the top-left corner, water damage has faded the ink and darkened the papyrus. The lack of ink in the top-right corner suggests that the papyrus contains remnants of the first eleven lines of the original."
