    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "A very fragmentarily-preserved letter describing local turmoil.\nRecto: Due to the poor condition of the papyrus only single words and short phrases are legible. The word all\u0101h in line 1 suggests a pious formula. Line 4: wa-qad q\u0101ma il\u0101; line 6: wa-\u2019l-n\u0101s \u02bfindana f\u012b harj wa-marj; line 7: ilayka; line 9: r\u0101ji\u02bf\u016bn.\nVerso: There is some ink on the verso, but the connection with the recto remains uncertain.\n"
    },
    {
      "label": "Diacritical dots",
      "value": "There are some diacritical dots."
    }
